cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper presents a new control method for soft robot snakes using deep reinforcement learning and central pattern generators. The focus is on achieving adaptive goal-reaching behaviors with changing goals, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep neural networks for reinforcement learning also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The central pattern generator system is a type of control system commonly used in robotics (cs.SY), and the adaptation of the option-critic framework for improved learning performance suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE).
